    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ariadne-entry\"><p><strong>Source:</strong> Ariadne's Book of Legends - Alpha v1.2, p. 28-31.</p><p>Devastating Strike</p><p>When you reach 20th level, you learn to channel your immense strength into a singular, devastating strike. You can use your action and expend 1 Legendary Point to make a melee weapon attack roll against a target within range. On a hit, you deal 5d12 x 5 damage of the weapon’s type. This attack does not benefit from any bonus to its damage. On a critical hit, you do not multiply the damage dice by 2, but instead deal 7d12 x 5 weapon damage.</p><p>A creature hit by Devastating Strike must succeed on a Constitution saving throw against your Strength score or become Impaired for a minute.</p><p>5.5e: If you use Reckless Attack on your Devastating Strike, you can forgo any Advantage on the attack roll. The Multiplier Attack must not have Disadvantage. If the attack hits, you add 1 die to the Devastating Strike’s damage equation, and you can cause two Brutal Strike effects of your choice. If the attack misses, you can</p><p>Points Rages Rage Damage</p><p>Weapon Mastery</p><p>expend 1 use of your Rage to reroll the attack. You must use the new roll.</p></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
